answers.body_markdown:
I suggest not to use **non-null assertion operator `!!`** in places where a variable can be `null`. There is a **safe call operator `?.`** for that purpose:

    val pictureUrl = response.body()?.picurl
    pictureUrl?.let { picurl -&gt;
        // Execute this block of code only when `pictureUrl` is not null
            val updateCheck = UpdateTaskA(
            this@UserImageCropActivity, 
            picurl, 
            userResponse.id 
        ).execute().get()
    }

